<TITLE> Bangladesh hockey team lose 4-2 to Russia </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 25 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh national hockey team showed a little improvement in the Four-nation Invitation Hockey Tournament when they went 4-2 down to hosts Russia in their second match in Moscow on Thursday. Rasel Mahmud Jimmy and Golam Mostafa Manik scored one goal each for Bangladesh, who suffered a massive 8-0 loss to South Africa in their first match on Wednesday, in the chilly Russian weather, according to a SMS from team manager Anvir Ahmed. Bangladesh will play their next match against world 11-ranked Canada on June 27 bdn
